column1: #Text=If you do n’t enjoy what you are doing , you should n’t be there .
#Text=DS : What ’s the difference between obedience and submission ?
#Text=Obedience , I would say , is not as intense as submission .
#Text=Submission is they want to serve you and have you be a Goddess to them .
#Text=They are doing it willingly , whereas obedience is ‘ ’ you have to ’ ’
#Text=Submission is more they want to do it .
#Text=I feel like obedience is completing tasks for somebody —
#Text=Yeah , “ Go get me a glass of milk ! ” [ Laughs ]
#Text=But submission is , “ I am going to put my foot in your face and have you lick the bottom of my boot ! ”
#Text=DS : How do you know that line between personal and impersonal in such a personal experience ?
#Text=First , we do n’t get a real chance to talk to them .
#Text=They just want a fantasy and a lot of time they do n’t want you to know the motivations behind it , because maybe they are a little disturbed by it .
#Text=You only have a small window to chat with them at the end , and it ’s usually superficial .
#Text=You want them to maintain the idea of who you are .
#Text=You never ever want to let them know who you are , really , because that would snatch the fantasy of this power woman who is here because she enjoys making men feel like shit !
#Text=Yeah , let me tell you about my cats !
#Text=I like Art History and I talk to people about that , about galleries and museums .
#Text=DS : Do you think BDSM leads to domestic violence at all ?
#Text=It ’s the media that makes that connection , but I honestly have not ever heard of it .
#Text=It goes against everything S&M is , which is about consent , about the fact that you have somebody giving themselves to you .
#Text=It ’s why we even have these safe words here .
#Text=It ’s for the fact that if anything goes above and beyond anything they want , you can just say , “ Now I want you to stop . ”
#Text=You want to give people the level of pain that THEY want , so it ’s not about going off on people and beating the crap out of them willy-nilly without consent .
#Text=Sometimes if they want to be taken past that level of pain they have experienced before , and they get into deep , deep places , you hurt them more than they are used to .

#Text=But I ’m not here because I want to take my aggressions out on them , although some of the real serious people ARE sort of vampires like that and really want you to hate them and take aggression out on them .
#Text=You ca n’t really group the clients in one cluster .
#Text=Most of them who come in here are really smart , intellectual people —
